And the First Antiphon is sung by the chanters. And the priest says the prayer of the Antiphon, (but some
 say it before the exclamation). But the deacon, bowing, leaves his place and goes to stand before the icon of Christ, holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keep\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\i\fs32\insrsid8659437 People}{\i\fs36\insrsid8659437 :}{\fs36\insrsid8659437  }{\fs32\insrsid8659437 
Bless the Lord, O my soul; blessed art Thou, O Lord./
\par Bless the Lord, O my soul, and all that is within me bless His holy name./
\par Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all that He hath done for thee./
\par Who is gracious unto all thine iniquities, Who healeth all thine infirmities./
\par Who redeemeth thy life from corruption, Who crowneth thee with mercy and compassion./
\par Who fulfilleth thy desire with good things; thy youth shall be renewed as the eagle's./
\par The Lord performeth deeds of mercy, and executeth judgment for all them that are wronged. He hath made His ways known unto Moses, unto the sons of Israel the things that He hath willed./
\par Compassionate and merciful is the Lord, long\_suffering and plenteous in mercy./
\par Not unto the end will He be angered, neither unto eternity will He be wroth. Not according to our iniquities hath He dealt with us, neither according to our sins hath He rewarded us./
\par For according to the height of heaven from the earth, the Lord hath made His mercy to prevail over them that fear Him./
\par As far as the east is from the west, so far hath He removed our iniquities from us./
\par Like as a father hath compassion upon His sons, so hath the Lord had compassion upon them that fear Him;/
\par for He knoweth whereof we are made, He hath remembered that we are dust./
\par As for man, his days are as the grass; as a flower of the field, so shall he blossom forth./
\par For when the wind is passed over it, then it shall be gone, and no longer will it know the place thereof./
\par But the mercy of the Lord is from eternity, even unto eternity, upon them that fear Him./
\par And His righteousness is upon sons of sons, upon them that keep His testament and remember His commandments to do them./
\par The Lord in heaven hath prepared His throne, and His kingdom ruleth over all./
\par Bless the Lord, all ye His angels, mighty in strength, that perform His word, to hear the voice of His words./
\par Bless the Lord, all ye His hosts, His ministers that do His will./
\par Bless the Lord, all ye His works, in every place of His dominion.
\par Glory to the Father,/ and to the Son,/ and to the Holy Spirit. Both now and ever,/ and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par Bless the Lord, O my soul,/ and all that is within me/ bless His holy name;/ blessed art Thou, O Lord.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs28\insrsid8659437 
