\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs36\insrsid8659437 Praise the Lord, O my soul./
\par  I will praise the Lord in my life,/
\par  I will chant unto my God for as long as I have my being./
\par  Trust ye not in princes, in the sons of men,/
\par  in whom there is no salvation,/
\par  His spirit shall go forth,/
\par  and he shall return unto his earth./
\par  In that day all his thoughts shall perish./
\par  Blessed is he of whom the God of Jacob is his help,/
\par  whose hope is in the Lord his God./
\par  Who hath made heaven and the earth,/
\par  the sea and all that is therein./
\par  Who keepeth truth unto eternity,/
\par  Who executeth judgment for the wronged,/
\par  Who giveth food unto the hungry./
\par  The Lord looseth the fettered;/
\par  the Lord maketh wise the blind;/
\par  the Lord setteth aright the fallen;/
\par  the Lord loveth the righteous;/
\par  The Lord preserveth the proselytes./
\par  He shall adopt for His own the orphan and widow,/
\par  and the way of sinners shall He destroy./
\par  The Lord shall be king unto eternity;/
\par  thy God, O Sion, unto generation and generation.
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Only\_begotten Son and Word of God, Who art immortal,/
\par  yet didst deign for our salvation/
\par  to be incarnate of the holy Theotokos and Ever\_Virgin Mary,/
\par  and without change didst become man,/
\par  and wast crucified, O Christ God, trampling down death by death,/
\par  Thou Who art one of the Holy Trinity,/
\par  glorified with the Father and the Holy Spirit, save us.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\insrsid8659437 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {\footerr \pard\plain \qc \li360\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 
