body, for the averting of everything hostile, for the enlightenment of the eyes of my heart, for the peace of the powers of my soul, for faith unashamed, for love unfeigned, for the fullness of wisdom, for the keeping of Thy commandments, for an increase 
o
f Thy divine grace, and for the attainment of Thy Kingdom; that being preserved by Them in Thy holiness I may ever remember Thy grace, and no longer live for myself but for Thee our Master and Benefactor. And thus when I have departed this life in hope of
 
eternal life, may I attain unto everlasting rest, where the sound of them that keep festival is unceasing and the delight is endless of them that behold the ineffable beauty of Thy countenance. For Thou art the true desire and the unutterable gladness of 
those who love Thee, O Christ our God, and all creation doth hymn Thee unto the ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid8659437 Of St. Basil the Great, 2: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
O Master Christ our God, King of the ages and Creator of all things, I thank Thee for all the good things Thou hast bestowed upon me and
 for the communion of Thy most pure and life-giving Mysteries. I pray Thee, therefore, O Good One and Lover of mankind: Keep me under Thy protection and in the shadow of Thy wings and grant me, even unto my last breath, to partake worthily, with a pure co
n
science, of Thy holy Things unto the remission of sins and life eternal. For Thou art the Bread of Life, the Source of Holiness, the Giver of good things, and unto Thee do we send up glory, together with the Father and the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and t
o the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid8659437 Verses of Metaphrastes, 3: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 O Thou Who givest me willingly Thy Flesh as food, \line 
Thou Who art fire, that doth consume the unworthy, \line Burn me not, O my Creator, \line But rather enter Thou into my members,\line Into all my joints, my reigns, my heart. \line Burn up the thorns of all my sins. \line 
Purify my soul, sanctify my thoughts. \line Strengthen my substance together with my bones. \line Enlighten the my simple five senses. \line Nail down the whole of me with Thy fear. \line Ever protect, preserve, and keep me \line From 
every soul-corrupting deed and word. \line Purify and cleanse and adorn me; \line Make me comely, give me understanding and enlighten me. \line Make me the dwelling-place of Thy Spirit alone, \line And no longer a habitation of sin, \line 
That from me as Thine abode through the entry of Communion \line Every evildoer, every passion may flee from me as from fire. \line As intercessors I offer unto Thee all the saints,\line The Commanders of the Bodiless Hosts, \line 
Thy Forerunner, the wise Apostles, \line And Thine undefiled pure Mother, \line Whose entreaties do Thou accept, O my compassionate Christ. \line And make Thy servant a child of light. \line For Thou alone art our sanctification, O Good One, \line 
And the radiance of our souls, \line And to Thee as our God and Master,\line We all send up glory as is meet, every day. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid8659437 Another Prayer: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
O Lord Jesus Christ our God, may Thy Holy Body, be unto me for life eternal, and Thy Precious Blood for the remission of sins; And may this Eucharist be to me for joy, health, and gladness. And at Thy dread Second Coming, vouchsafe me, a sinner, t
o stand at the right hand of Thy glory, through the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother and of all Thy Saints. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid8659437 Another Prayer, To the Most Holy Theotokos: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
All-holy Lady, Theotokos, light of my darkened soul, my hope, protection, refuge, consolation, my
 joy; I thank thee that thou hast vouchsafed me, who am unworthy, to be a partaker of the most pure Body and precious Blood of thy Son. O thou who gavest birth to the true Light, do thou enlighten the spiritual eyes of my heart; thou who didst gavest birt
h
 to the Source of Immortality, revive me who am dead in sin; thou who art the loving-compassionately Mother of the merciful God, have mercy on me and grant me compunction and contrition in my heart, and humility in my thoughts, and the recall of my though
t
s from their captivity. And vouchsafe me until my last breath to receive without condemnation the sanctification of the most Pure Mysteries for the healing of soul and body; And grant me tears of repentance and confession, with which to hymn and glorify t
hee all the days of my life; For blessed and glorified art Thou unto the ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid8659437 Then: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
Now lettest Thou Thy servant depart in peace, O Master, according to Thy word: for mine eyes have seen Thy salvation, which Thou hast prepared before the face of all peoples; a light of revelation for the Gentiles, and the glory of Thy people Israel. 

\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal : have mercy on us }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8659437 Thrice.}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  
\par Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
All-holy Trinity, have mercy on us. Lord, cleanse us from our sins. Master, Pardon our iniquities. Holy God, visit and heal our infirmities for thy Name's sake. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 Lord, have mercy }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8659437 Thrice.}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
Our Father, who art in the heavens, hallowed be thy Name; thy kingdom come; thy will be done on earth, as it is in heaven. Give us this day our daily bread; and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and 
lead us not into temptation. but deliver us from the Evil One. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 
\par Priest:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s58\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid8659437 
\par }\pard \s58\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid8659437 Troparion to St Basil, First Tone:
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 
\par Reader:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437 
 Thy fame has gone forth into all the earth,/ which has received thy word./ Thereby thou hast taught the Faith; thou hast revealed the nature of created things;/ thou hast made a royal priesthood of the ordered life of men./ Righteous Fathe
r Basil, intercede with Christ our God/ that our souls may be saved.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437  Glory... 
\par }\pard\plain \s58\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid8659437 Kontakion, Fourth Tone:}{\cs44\i0\fs28\insrsid8659437  
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 
Thou wast an unshaken foundation of the Church/ and didst give to all mortals an inviolate lordship/ which thou didst seal with thy doctrine,/ O righteous Basil, / revealer of the mysteries of heaven.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 Both now... 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32\insrsid8659437 O protection of Christians that cannot be put to shame, O Mediation unto the Creator unfailing: Disdain not the suppliant voices of
 sinners; but be thou quick, O good one, to help us who in faith cry unto Thee; hasten to intercession and speed thou to make supplication, thou who dost ever protect, O Theotokos, them that honor thee. 
\par Lord, have mercy }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8659437 12 Times}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Priest:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  }{\cs47\b\fs36\insrsid8659437 Most Holy Theotokos save us! 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Reader: }{\fs32\insrsid8659437 
More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim, thee who without defilement gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Priest:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  }{\cs47\b\fs36\insrsid8659437 Glory to Thee, O Christ, our God and our hope, glory to Thee.}{
\fs32\insrsid8659437  
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Reader: }{\fs32\insrsid8659437 Glory... Both now.. Lord have mercy Thrice Father bless! 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Priest:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  }{\cs47\b\fs36\insrsid8659437 May Christ our true God
 (Who rose from the dead), through the intercessions of His most pure Mother; and of all the Saints, have mercy upon us and save us, for He is good and the Lover of mankind. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid8659437 Reader:}{\fs32\insrsid8659437  Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6\insrsid8659437 Then, those who have received the Divine Mysteries approach to kis
s the Cross.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid6357474 
